upergroup" data-id=3D"hab_what-is-a-supergroup"></a><br><p class=3D"font-no=
rmal ">A Supergroup is a group created dynamically based on shared attribut=
es in Rippling. Instead of including individual people by name, you can mak=
e a Supergroup based on attributes such as department, location, tenure, em=
ployment status, or course certification status, and people who share those=
 attributes will automatically be included in the group.</p><br><p class=3D=
"font-normal ">The members of a Supergroup are updated automatically when t=
he attributes in Rippling change. Say an employee gets promoted, switches d=
epartments, or leaves the company=E2=80=94that employee will automatically =
be included in Supergroups that match their new attributes and excluded fro=
m Supergroups where their attributes no longer match.</p><br><p class=3D"fo=
nt-normal ">Supergroups let you utilize your employee data in Rippling to a=
utomate access across the system, saving time, eliminating manual errors, a=
nd ensuring people always have what they need when they need it.</p><br><p =
class=3D"font-normal ">Anywhere in Rippling that you see the Include/Except=
 box, you can set up a Supergroup.</p><br><img class=3D"shadow-md border bo=
rder-opacity-25 my-4" alt=3D"945615220635_Answer_1.jpg" src=3D"https://imag=
es.ctfassets.net/qlrvxw8mxga3/3QdeiXE0zblQ0h14hv09q9/04eed642468e0db3641951=
6bd3a7c2d5/945615220635_Answer_1.jpg"><br><a class=3D"absolute opacity-0 sc=
roll-mt-40" id=3D"attributes-you-can-use-when-defining-supergroups" data-id=
=3D"hat_attributes-you-can-use-when-defining-supergroups"></a><h2 class=3D"=
text-4xl font-bold" id=3D"attributes-you-can-use-when-defining-supergroups"=
 data-id=3D"attributes-you-can-use-when-defining-supergroups">Attributes yo=
u can use when defining Supergroups</h2><a class=3D"absolute mt-20 opacity-=
0" id=3D"attributes-you-can-use-when-defining-supergroups" data-id=3D"hab_a=
ttributes-you-can-use-when-defining-supergroups"></a><br><p class=3D"font-n=
ormal ">Any attribute in the Rippling data model can be used to define a Su=
pergroup. Here are just a few examples of the attributes you can use:</p><b=
r><ul class=3D"list-disc pl-8"><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-n=
ormal ">Department, team, or level</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p cla=
ss=3D"font-normal ">Work location</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p clas=
s=3D"font-normal ">Country, state, or city of residence</p></li><li class=
=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Employment type or status</p></l=
i><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Compensation details<=
/p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Whether or not =
someone is a manager or admin</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D=
"font-normal ">Whether or not someone is currently on leave</p></li><li cla=
ss=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Type of device someone is assi=
gned</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Someone=E2=
=80=99s pay frequency</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-no=
rmal ">Someone=E2=80=99s work relationships, such as who their peers are, w=
ho their manager is, or their work relationship to a specific person</p></l=
i><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Custom fields you=E2=
=80=99ve added to Rippling</p></li></ul><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">Super=
groups can be as simple or as complicated as you need them to be to target =
the right people. For example, this Supergroup includes everyone in the Mar=
keting department:</p><br><img class=3D"shadow-md border border-opacity-25 =
my-4" alt=3D"945615220635_Answer_2.jpg" src=3D"https://images.ctfassets.net=
/qlrvxw8mxga3/6c7LzxDvuHDqDYuxJUeIin/18358132ee20fc767d32af3455358f98/94561=
5220635_Answer_2.jpg"><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">This Supergroup include=
s everyone in the Marketing department who is on the Events team except for=
 1099 contractors.</p><br><img class=3D"shadow-md border border-opacity-25 =
my-4" alt=3D"945615220635_Answer_3.jpg" src=3D"https://images.ctfassets.net=
/qlrvxw8mxga3/3D5KSGCmA4jfs1sUX8XEdI/375fb8e4f5479e747fafe3ec2808672b/94561=
5220635_Answer_3.jpg"><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">Learn more in <a class=
=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 hover:cursor-pointer" href=3D"https://help.ri=
ppling.com/article?articleId=3D53273402848">our article about how to define=
 a Supergroup</a>.</p><br><div class=3D"my-2 border border-solid rounded-md=
 p-4 md:py-4 md:grid md:grid-cols-10  border-[#D3DBEC] bg-[#F6F8FB]  "><div=
 class=3D"hidden md:col-span-1 md:flex justify-center"> <img class=3D"h-6" =
src=3D"https://static-assets.ripplingcdn.com/bizsys/hc_functional-icons/not=
eIcons/hc_information.png" alt=3D"Information"> </div><div class=3D"md:col-=
span-9"><p class=3D"font-normal text-gray-700"></p><p class=3D"font-normal =
"><b>Note</b>: You can also create device-based Supergroups when configurin=
g your managed devices. These groups can be based on device attributes such=
 as operating system version, assignment status, asset tag, or the presence=
 of a certain configuration profile. Learn more in <a class=3D"font-normal =
text-blue-600 hover:cursor-pointer" href=3D"https://help.rippling.com/artic=
le?articleId=3D10422235842">our article about using Supergroups to configur=
e managed devices</a>.</p><p></p></div></div><br><a class=3D"absolute opaci=
ty-0 scroll-mt-40" id=3D"use-cases-for-supergroups" data-id=3D"hat_use-case=
s-for-supergroups"></a><h2 class=3D"text-4xl font-bold" id=3D"use-cases-for=
-supergroups" data-id=3D"use-cases-for-supergroups">Use cases for Supergrou=
ps</h2><a class=3D"absolute mt-20 opacity-0" id=3D"use-cases-for-supergroup=
s" data-id=3D"hab_use-cases-for-supergroups"></a><br><p class=3D"font-norma=
l ">Here are a few more examples of how you can use Supergroups to automate=
 and optimize group management in Rippling.</p><br><ul class=3D"list-disc p=
l-8"><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Set up a workflow =
that sends a scheduled report to the members of the Sales department. Even =
if the actual members of the Sales department change, Rippling will continu=
e to send the report to the right people without the need to modify the wor=
kflow.</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Create a=
 permission profile that=E2=80=99s assigned to all of your Director-level e=
mployees. When an employee is promoted to Director, they=E2=80=99ll automat=
ically inherit the permission profile that gives them the access they need.=
</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Set up a data =
access policy for Zendesk that lets managers in the Customer Service depart=
ment use data from your Zendesk tickets to trigger workflows in Rippling. W=
hen Customer Service agents are promoted to manager, they=E2=80=99ll automa=
tically get access to use Zendesk data in workflows.</p></li><li class=3D"i=
tems-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Set a policy that gives access to the=
 AWS Admin group only to engineers of level 6 or 7 who have at least one ye=
ar of tenure, use a security key to sign in to Rippling, and have an HIPAA =
certification. When engineers' attributes change to meet these criteria, th=
ey're automatically added to the group.</p><img class=3D"shadow-md border b=
order-opacity-25 my-4" alt=3D"945615220635_Answer_4.jpg" src=3D"https://ima=
ges.ctfassets.net/qlrvxw8mxga3/3mKBBUxRLZxcgdhstZWFvm/4f1dda5fed5df65ddc2d8=
d683ba601ec/945615220635_Answer_4.jpg"><p class=3D"font-normal ">&nbsp;</p>=
</li></ul><br><a class=3D"absolute opacity-0 scroll-mt-40" id=3D"methods-fo=
r-creating-supergroups" data-id=3D"hat_methods-for-creating-supergroups"></=
a><h2 class=3D"text-4xl font-bold" id=3D"methods-for-creating-supergroups" =
data-id=3D"methods-for-creating-supergroups">Methods for creating Supergrou=
ps</h2><a class=3D"absolute mt-20 opacity-0" id=3D"methods-for-creating-sup=
ergroups" data-id=3D"hab_methods-for-creating-supergroups"></a><br><p class=
=3D"font-normal ">There are two different ways you can create Supergroups:<=
/p><br><ul class=3D"list-disc pl-8"><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"f=
ont-normal ">You can <b>save</b> them in the Saved Supergroups app and then=
 use them throughout Rippling wherever the Supergroups box is available. Th=
is is a good option if you want to ensure your groups are managed consisten=
tly across Rippling. Learn how to <a class=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 hov=
er:cursor-pointer" href=3D"https://help.rippling.com/article?articleId=3D37=
0084709203">create a saved Supergroup</a>.</p></li><li class=3D"items-start=
"><p class=3D"font-normal ">You can create a Supergroup <b>on the fly</b> a=
nywhere you see the Supergroups box. For example, when setting up a workflo=
w that sends an email, you can create a Supergroup right within the workflo=
w to define the recipients of the email. This is a good option for one-off =
groups that don=E2=80=99t need to be reused or regularly audited.</p></li><=
/ul><br><div class=3D"my-2 border border-solid rounded-md p-4 md:py-4 md:gr=
id md:grid-cols-10  border-[#D3DBEC] bg-[#F6F8FB]  "><div class=3D"hidden m=
d:col-span-1 md:flex justify-center"> <img class=3D"h-6" src=3D"https://sta=
tic-assets.ripplingcdn.com/bizsys/hc_functional-icons/noteIcons/hc_informat=
ion.png" alt=3D"Information"> </div><div class=3D"md:col-span-9"><p class=
=3D"font-normal text-gray-700"></p><p class=3D"font-normal "><b>Note</b>: E=
mployee-based Supergroups can be created in the Saved Supergroups app. Devi=
ce-based Supergroups can only be created on the fly when setting up device =
configurations.</p><p></p></div></div><br><a class=3D"absolute opacity-0 sc=
roll-mt-40" id=3D"overview-of-the-saved-supergroups-app" data-id=3D"hat_ove=
rview-of-the-saved-supergroups-app"></a><h2 class=3D"text-4xl font-bold" id=
=3D"overview-of-the-saved-supergroups-app" data-id=3D"overview-of-the-saved=
-supergroups-app">Overview of the Saved Supergroups app</h2><a class=3D"abs=
olute mt-20 opacity-0" id=3D"overview-of-the-saved-supergroups-app" data-id=
=3D"hab_overview-of-the-saved-supergroups-app"></a><br><p class=3D"font-nor=
mal ">To visit the Saved Supergroups app, open the Rippling sidebar and sel=
ect <b>Settings</b> &gt; <b>Saved Supergroups</b>.</p><br><img class=3D"sha=
dow-md border border-opacity-25 my-4" alt=3D"945615220635_Answer_5.jpg" src=
=3D"https://images.ctfassets.net/qlrvxw8mxga3/7aScdKEvlVDFHEszmHYPSC/6904dc=
dfb2089f6a145206afd613ec42/945615220635_Answer_5.jpg"><br><ul class=3D"list=
-disc pl-8"><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">The <b>Save=
d Supergroups</b> tab contains a list of your saved Supergroups.</p></li><l=
i class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">The <b>Groups to migrate<=
/b> tab contains a list of Supergroups that were created on the fly to defi=
ne groups within integrated apps (think Google groups, Slack channels, Micr=
osoft security groups, etc.). Rippling recommends migrating these to be sav=
ed Supergroups. Learn more in <a class=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 hover:c=
ursor-pointer" href=3D"https://help.rippling.com/article?articleId=3D784843=
857967">our article about how to migrate integration groups</a>.</p></li></=
ul><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">Your permission profile assignments and ac=
cess settings on specific saved Supergroups determine whether or not you ca=
n access the Saved Supergroups app.</p><br><a class=3D"absolute opacity-0 s=
croll-mt-40" id=3D"see-also" data-id=3D"hat_see-also"></a><h2 class=3D"text=
-4xl font-bold" id=3D"see-also" data-id=3D"see-also">See also</h2><a class=
=3D"absolute mt-20 opacity-0" id=3D"see-also" data-id=3D"hab_see-also"></a>=
<br><ul class=3D"list-disc pl-8"><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font=
